 <title>Getting Started</title>

 <itemizedlist>
  <para>To use connectors in your application, first download the <link
  xlink:href="http://openicf.forgerock.org/downloads.html" xlink:show="new"
  >Connector Framework</link>. Next, add the following jars to your
  CLASSPATH:</para>
  <listitem>
   <para><filename>connector-framework.jar</filename> (compile and runtime
   dependency)</para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem>
   <para><filename>connector-framework-internal.jar</filename> (runtime
   dependency only)</para>
  </listitem>
 </itemizedlist>

 <para>Also download the Connector Bundles you need, and add them to the
 CLASSPATH as well. At this point you can start using the connectors in your
 application.</para>

 <para>You can also download builds from the <link
 xlink:href="http://openicf.forgerock.org/downloads.html"
 xlink:show="new">OpenICF download page</link>.</para>
</chapter>
